headline: Is AI-Fueled Growth And The CommScope Deal Altering The Investment Case For Amphenol (APH)?
summary: Amphenol recently reported record Q3 2025 results, with revenue and earnings rising sharply on surging AI data center demand and raised guidance for Q4 and full-year 2025. The company also announced a large 52% dividend increase from January 2026 and a planned US$10.50 billion CommScope Connectivity and Cable Solutions acquisition that would significantly expand its AI, communications infrastructure, and defense exposure. headline: What The Latest Wall Street Rerating Means For Amphenol’s Valuation Story
summary: Amphenol’s fair value estimate has nudged higher to about $148.15 from roughly $147.99 as analysts grow more confident that the company can deliver stronger long term revenue growth, supported by better than expected Q3 results and rising forecasts for FY25 sales in the low $20B range.
